</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER><HI>Elm.</HI></SPEAKER>
<L>What vanity</L>
<L>Have I betray'd, what ba&s;ene&s;s, what pre&s;umption,</L>
<L>To need &s;o &s;trange a trial? If you doubt</L>
<L>My loyalty, and think I entertain</L>
<L><PB N="39" REF="38">De&s;igns injurious to my Sov'reign's honour,</L>
<L>And your fair virtue&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER><HI>Q.</HI></SPEAKER>
<L>'Tis too much, my Lord,</L>
<L>This diffidence, this cold re&s;erve&mdash;You urge me</L>
<L>To what I wou'd avoid, beyond the bounds</L>
<L>I had pre&s;crib'd my&s;elf: Yes, I cou'd die</L>
