<DIV1 TYPE="epilogue">
<PB REF="71">
<HEAD>EPILOGUE.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>Spoken by Mr. MILWARD.</BYLINE>
<L>YOU, who &s;upreme o'er ev'ry work of Wit,</L>
<L>In Judgment here unaw'd, unbia&s;t &s;it,</L>
<L>The <HI>Palatines</HI> and <HI>Guardians</HI> of the Pit;</L>
<L>If to your minds this meerly-modern Play,</L>
<L>No u&s;eful &s;en&s;e, no gen'rous warmth convey;</L>
<L>If <HI>Fu&s;tian</HI> here, thro' each unnat'ral Scene,</L>
<L>In &s;train'd conceits <HI>&s;ound high,</HI> and <HI>nothing mean;</HI></L>
<L>If <HI>Lofty Dulne&s;s</HI> for your Vengeance call;</L>
<L>Like <HI>Elmerick Judge,</HI> and let the <HI>Guilty Fall</HI>.</L>
<L>But if Simplicity with Force and Fire,</L>
<L>Unlabour'd thoughts and artle&s;s words in&s;pire;</L>
<L>If, like the Action which the&s;e Scenes relate,</L>
<L>The whole appear irregularly Great;</L>
<L>If ma&s;ter-&s;trokes the nobler Pa&s;&s;ions move,</L>
<L>Then, like the <HI>King, acquit</HI> us, and <HI>approve</HI>.</L>
<TRAILER>The END.</TRAILER>
